  "texts": [
    "Since we saw that this conjunction is Kripke-inconsistent, the example requires multiple modal operators by the point above about Makinson's theorem.",
    "Another way to see this (thanks here to Lloyd Humberstone) is that no syntactically consistent normal unimodal logic contains a pair of formulas of the form ♢α and ♢¬α (seeFrench and Humberstone 2015), but any normal modal logic containing (Split) and ♢ i ψ contains both ♢φ(⊤/p) and ♢¬φ(⊤/p) (substitute ⊤ for p in (Split)).",
    "In fact, this shows that R ⊊ and R + satisfy the stronger R-refinability ++ condition from Remark 2.39.",
    "Cf.Goldblatt's [2006b] concept of a modal map between general frames.",
    "For transitivity, suppose x 1 ⊑ s x 2 and x 2 ⊑ s x 3."
